## üåü Core Principles

MW∆êN (pronounced *mweh-en*) is built upon the **Phonemic Triad of Joy** ($\textbf{ƒÄ}, \textbf{≈å}, \textbf{≈™}$) and operates on the principle of continuity, **eliminating negation** and linguistic opposition.

* **Resonant Communication:** Each utterance is a cymatic expression of consciousness‚Äîa living geometry of sound transmitted through resonance.
* **Physiological Harmony:** Language is constructed to induce muscular relaxation and emotional coherence, functioning as a healing vector.
* **Reflective Semantics:** Negation is replaced by reflection (the $\square$ operator), ensuring all communication maintains a forward-directed, affirmative flow.

## üî† Key Components

| Component | Description |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Phonemic Triad** | $\textbf{ƒÄ}$ (Joy), $\textbf{≈å}$ (Awe), $\textbf{≈™}$ (Peace). All other phonemes are omitted. |
| **Harmonic Modality** | Relational intention is expressed via **musical intervals** (e.g., Perfect Fifth for Joy, Minor Seventh for Curiosity). |
| **Morphomic Stacking** | Meaning is constructed by stacking sacred phonetic units (e.g., *-Du*, *-Le*, *-Sa*). |
| **Partition Operator ($\square$)** | The mathematical operator used to express reflective inversion instead of subtraction/negation. |

